AT&T Inc And International Business Machines Corp To Deliver A Fully Managed Ecommerce Solution For Retailers

Thursday, 6 Jun 2013 05:59pm EDT

AT&T Inc and International Business Machines Corp announced a business agreement to deliver a new eCommerce solution that can help retailers provide a consistent shopping experience for customers whether they are shopping online, via a mobile app or in-store. The new service, expected to be available this year, combines AT&T's cloud, application management and network services with eCommerce software from IBM's Smarter Commerce initiative in a single, subscription-based package designed for retailers. To meet the rising demand of digitally-savvy consumers, IBM and AT&T are working together to provide retailers with an eCommerce suite that will improve the online consumer shopping experience and make it easier to browse and buy products any time through any channel, offering retailers several benefits.Â 

